The system begins with the Input Image Data Module, which supplies image pixel values to the FPGA processing pipeline.
  The Image Processing Module analyzes the incoming pixel data and prepares it for inspection through grayscale processing and feature extraction.
  The Threshold Comparison Module compares pixel intensities against predefined reference values to identify abnormal regions.
  Extracted features such as shape, size, and area are then evaluated by the Defect Detection Module.
  Based on this analysis, the Output Module generates a defect status signal indicating whether the inspected object is defective or non-defective
  The entire design is implemented using Verilog/VHDL and verified through simulation in Quartus Prime.

